<TITLE> Pakistan veterans to toughen rules after 2nd death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 KARACHI, May 21 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Pakistan's veterans cricket association will toughen eligibility requirements following the deaths of two players in Karachi this year. Former first class cricketer Javed Sheikh, 53, died after complaining of chest pain after bowling three overs in a night match on Tuesday. His death follows that of Fakhir Khairi, a doctor, who died from cardiac arrest during a veterans match earlier this year. "We definitely will be setting new guidelines to ensure players with cardiac problems and serious medical history don't play in these senior tournaments," Fawad Ijaz, the president of the veterans cricket association, said. "These veteran cricket tournaments are supposed to be positive activities .... we don't want to see such tragedies.
